The Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, has called for the immediate establishment of the Electoral Offences Tribunal as part of its measures to stem election malpractices and deepen democracy in the country. The Chairman of the commission, Prof. Mahmood Yakubu, made the call on Tuesday in Abuja at a meeting of the Inter-Agency Consultative Committee on Election Security (ICCES). This is as the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Mr. Mohammed Adamu, represented by the DIG Operations, Abdulmajid Ali, said the Police made 58 high profile arrests during the just concluded 2019 general elections. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Electoral offences tribunal necessary — INEC IGP assures INEC of security for elections Only one party submitted 2019 election expense report — INEC Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin